-- 286	Define the function $f(x) = (4x -6)^{10}$. The function $f(x)$ can be represented as $a_{10} x^{10}+a_9x^9+\\cdots+a_1x+a_0$. Let $S = a_9 + a_7 + a_5 + a_3 + a_1$. What is the remainder when $|S|$ is divided by $1000$?	$488$	\N	AsciiMath
-- 272	Joe has a cone-shaped pitcher full of pancake batter with a base of radius $6$ inches and a height of $16$ inches. Each pancake Joe makes is the exact same size: a cylinder with a radius of $4$ inches that is $\\frac{1}{2}$ inch thick. Assume that Joe's pancakes don't rise. After making breakfast this morning, Joe notices that the pitcher is now $\\frac{1}{3}$ full. How many pancakes did Joe make this morning?	16	\N	AsciiMath
-- 279	The number $\\overline{717A7B7C}$, where $A$, $B$, and $C$ are distinct integer digits, is divisible by $12$. If $x$ is the maximum possible value of $A+B+C$ and $y$ is the minimum possible value of $A+B+C$, find $x-y$.	15	\N	AsciiMath
-- 287	The Mustangs and the Colts are two of the $20$ soccer teams in the Horsey Soccer League. The league is randomly split into two divisions with $10$ teams in each. Find the probability that the Mustangs and the Colts are in different divisions.	$\\frac{10}{19}$	\N	AsciiMath
-- 285	Equilateral triangle $ABC$ with side length $20$ is constructed, and a circle is inscribed in it, tangent to sides $AB$, $BC$, and $AC$. A circular coin with radius $1$ is then tossed randomly onto the triangle. Given that the coin lands completely within the triangle, what is the probability that at least part of the coin lands outside the circle?	$1-\\frac{\\pi}{3\\sqrt{3}}$	\N	AsciiMath
-- 288	The number $717A7B7C$, where $A$, $B$, and $C$ are distinct integer digits, is divisible by $12$. If $x$ is the maximum possible value of $A+B+C$ and $y$ is the minimum possible value of $A+B+C$, find $x-y$.	15	\N	AsciiMath
-- 296	Distinct digits $A$, $B$, and $C$ are chosen such that the six-digit number $7A7B7C$ is divisible by $12$. What is the largest possible value of $C$?	6	\N	AsciiMath
-- 289	Find the value of $x$ that satisfies the equation  $$\\sqrt{2 + \\sqrt{x + \\sqrt{2 + \\sqrt{x + ...}}}} = \\cfrac{15}{2 + \\cfrac{15}{2 + \\frac{15}{2 + ...}}}.$$	46	\N	AsciiMath
-- 295	Two circles $\\odot O_1$ and $\\odot O_2$ are drawn such that each circle passes through the center of the other circle. $\\odot O_1$ and $\\odot O_2$ intersect at points $A$ and $B$. Points $P$ and $Q$ are chosen independently and uniformly at random on $\\odot O_1$ and $\\odot O_2$, respectively. What is the probability that line segment $\\overline{PQ}$ intersects line segment $\\overline{AB}$?	$\\frac{4}{9}$	\N	AsciiMath
-- 290	Four consecutive positive integers have a product of $93024$. What is their sum?	70	\N	AsciiMath
-- 281	A race of aliens live on a flat world, with a source of light of negligible size (called the NUS) $100 \\text{ km}$ above the ground. One day, the NUS is too bright, and the aliens hope to build a bit of shade. They have a $150 \\text{ m} \\times 200 \\text{ m}$ board, and wish to cover an area of $75 \\text{ km}^2$ on the ground. Furthermore, while they have the powers of levitation, the aliens can only levitate the board parallel to the ground, as it becomes unstable otherwise. At how many kilometers above the ground do the aliens need to place the board in order to shade the desired area?	98	\N	AsciiMath
-- 299	Suppose $a$ and $b$ are real numbers such that the equation $x^4+ax^3+123x^2-123x+b=0$ has 4 distinct real solutions. Given that the sum of two of the solutions is $10$ and that the product of the other two solutions is $20$, find $a+b$.	-161	\N	AsciiMath
-- 292	For any real number $z$, let $\\lfloor z\\rfloor$ denote the greatest integer that is less than or equal to $z$. Find the area of the region formed by all points $(x,y)$ on the coordinate plane satisfying $x \\ge 0$, $y \\ge 0$, and $\\left\\lfloor{\\frac{x}{3}}\\right\\rfloor + \\left\\lfloor{\\frac{y}{3}}\\right\\rfloor = 9$.	90	\N	AsciiMath
-- 293	In the diagram below, $E$ lies on both $\\overline{AD}$ and $\\overline{BC}$. Given that $\\angle DAC = \\angle ADB$ and $[ABE] = 2[CDE] - 23$, find $[CDE]$. (Note that $[ABE]$ and $[CDE]$ refer to the areas of triangles $\\triangle ABE$ and $\\triangle CDE$, respectively.)\n\n\n\n<img src="https://i.imgur.com/rBxpQn0.png" width = 400>	23	\N	AsciiMath
-- 291	Let $n!$ denote the product of the integers between $1$ and $n$, inclusive. A positive integer divisor $d$ of $41!$ is chosen at random.  What is the probability that $d$ is divisible by $8$, but is not divisible by $16$?	$\\frac{1}{39}$	\N	AsciiMath
-- 297	Let $\\triangle{ABC}$ be a right triangle with $AB = 3$, $BC = 4$, and $CA = 5$. Let $D$ and $E$ be points on sides $BC$ and $AB$, respectively, such that $AD$ bisects $\\angle{A}$ and $CE$ bisects $\\angle{C}$. Define $F$ to be the intersection point of $AD$ and $CE$, and let $O$ be the circumcenter of $\\triangle{DEF}$. Find $BO$.	$\\frac{\\sqrt{2}}{12}$	\N	AsciiMath
-- 298	Find the greatest positive integer $n$ for which\n\\[ 2^{40} + 2^{32} + 2^{22} + 2^{21} + 2^{12} + 1 \\]\nis divisible by $5^n$.	8	\N	AsciiMath
-- 294	A sequence of integers is defined recursively by $a_0=0$ and $a_{n+1}=17a_n+1$ for all $n\\geq0$. Find the remainder when $a_{200}$ is divided by $2023$.	18	\N	AsciiMath
-- \.


