-- 25	2	Relay Rodeo	300	- This round contains 21 problems to be solved in 45 minutes.<br>\r\n- Problems are split into 4 sets of 5, with a final 'Boss' problem, that relies on the final answer to each set.<br>\r\n- Some of the problems refer to the answer to earlier problems in the same set.<br>\r\n- For example, problem 2 may begin with, “Let N be the answer\r\nto Problem 1.” So, Problem 2 can only be attempted after Problem 1 has been answered.<br>\r\n- Problems 5, 10, 15, and 20 are worth 3 points each. Problem 21 is worth 6 points. All other problems are worth 2 points each.	2024-09-29 09:05:00+00	Colt	{"pages": [""]}	2700	t	t	f	Standard
-- 18	3	COMP Practice Test	300	<p>These are some sample instructions!<br>\nWe highly recommend you read the instructions for the other tests that are available to you before the tournament as well.<br>\nCheck out <a href="https://asciimath.org/#syntax" target="_blank">AsciiMath</a> for information about how to format mathematical answers!<br>\nNote that for all tests, answers are automatically submitted when time runs out.\n</p>\n<p>Some tests also have multiple pages - once you continue from a page, you can't return!</p>	2024-09-26 21:41:34+00	\N	{"pages": ["Page 1", "Page 2"]}	259200	t	t	f	Standard
-- 15	3	Betting Bonanza	300	<p>In the <strong>Betting Bonanza</strong> round, teams will strategically bet on horse races and see who comes out on top.</p>\r\n<h4>Instructions</h4>\r\n<p>\r\n- This round contains 5 "races" (sets) consisting of 5 problems each to be solved in a total of 45 minutes.<br>\r\n- Teams begin the round with $100$ betting tokens that they can bet across the races as they choose. <br>\r\n- Prior to starting a race, teams will be able to wager tokens on the upcoming race. Each race has its own multiplier from 2.0, 2.5, 3.0, 3.5, and 4.0, with later races having harder questions and larger multipliers. <br>\r\n- For every question a team answers correctly in a set, they will earn the number of tokens that they wagered multiplied by the multiplier of the set they are working on.<br>\r\n- For example, if my team wagers $25$ tokens on Set $5$ (multiplier 4.0), and we get $3$ questions correct on Set $5$, we will earn $25\\cdot 3 \\cdot 4.0 = 300$ points on that set. <br>\r\n- Wagers on sets are <strong>final</strong>. Once you lock it in, you can't go back<br>\r\n- Once you submit a set, you cannot return to it, so make sure your answers are final before you continue!<br>\r\n- <strong style="color:red">Teams are required to keep track of how many tokens they have!</strong> Any tokens bet past $100$ will not be counted!<br>\r\n- Teams are NOT required to bet all of their tokens - any unbet tokens will be worth $1$ point.\r\n</p>\r\n<br>\r\n<h4>Strategy Tips</h4>\r\n<p>\r\n- Keep your team's skill level in mind! It can be advantageous to spend more points and time on the earlier races and make sure you get value out of your tokens, rather than saving them for later and solving only 1-2 questions in a race. You don't necessarily have to attempt the later races!<br>\r\n- Solving more problems on earlier races is generally better than fewer on later races (e.g. 5 problems on set 3 earns more points than 4 problems on set 4)<br>\r\n- Pay attention to how difficulty the previous race was - if you feel like you're reaching your solving limits, it might be time to go all-in on the next race and spend the rest of your time on it.<br>\r\n</p>	2024-09-28 19:10:00+00	Foal	{"pages": ["Race 1 Bet", "Race 1", "Race 2 Bet", "Race 2", "Race 3 Bet", "Race 3", "Race 4 Bet", "Race 4", "Race 5 Bet", "Race 5"]}	2700	t	t	f	Meltdown
-- 14	3	Meltdown Madness	300	<p><span style="color:red">The Floor is Lava!</span> The <strong>Meltdown Madness</strong> round contains 25 problems to be solved in 50 minutes. Be careful, however, as lava is rising and melting the problems! Strategize with your team to solve as many problems as you can before the lava claims them.</p><br>\r\n<h4>Instructions</h4>\r\n<p> \r\nEvery $2$ minutes, a problem will melt and sink into the lava, after which it can no longer be solved.<br>\r\nProblems melt in chronologically order, meaning that problem 1 will melt after the first two minutes, then problem 2 will melt after the next two minutes, and so on. The timer next to a problem indicates how long until it melts.<br>\r\nOnce a problem has sunk, you will not be able to change your answer on the problem.</p>\r\n<br>\r\n<h4>Strategy Tips</h4>\r\n<p>\r\n- Two minutes is not a lot of time to solve any individual problem! Figure out how to split problems and work together to solve as many easy problems as you can before they melt!<br>\r\n- At some point, problems may be sinking faster than you can solve them - if this happens, start aiming to solve every other problem, or every 3 problems, so you have more time to solve each one!<br>\r\n- Consider glancing through the remaining problems and work on the ones that look easy	2024-09-28 20:11:00+00	Stallion	{"pages": [""], "meltTime": 120}	3000	t	t	f	Meltdown
